oh-so-easy broccoli cheddar pot pies
http://ohmyveggies.com/recipe-oh-so-easy-broccoli-cheddar-pot-pies/

4 tbsp. unsalted butter
2 garlic cloves, minced
1 lg. onion, chopped
1 c. chopped celery
salt + pepper to taste
3 tbsp. all-purpose flour
1 c. reduced-fat (2%) milk
4 oz. shredded sharp cheddar cheese
pinch or two of cayenne (optional)
4 c. steamed broccoli florets (about 2 small heads of broccoli)
1 sheet puff pastry OR frozen pie crust
1 egg, whisked
oil mister or cooking spray
instructions

Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

In large saucepan over medium heat melt butter and saute garlic, onions, and
celery until softened, about 5 minutes.  Season with 1/2 tsp, salt and 1/2 tsp.
pepper.

Reduce heat to low and add flour.  Stir with wooden spoon until flour is
absorbed, about 1 minute.

Stir in milk.  Bring to a boil and stir 5 minutes until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese, bit at a time, until all cheese is
melted.  Stir in broccoli.

For individual ramekins:

Cut four pieces of puff pastry to fit tops of 3 and 1/2-inch ramekins OR
simply cut the pastry sheet into four equal squares. Cut an X in the middle of
each piece of puff pastry to vent steam.

Divide broccoli cheese mixture into ramekins that have been sprayed with
cooking spray or an oil mister. Top each with puff pastry. Brush puff pastry
with egg wash. Bake for 12-14 minutes or until puff pastry is puffy and golden
brown.

For a single pie:

Bake bottom crust according to directions.  Pour filling into baked crust.
Place bottom crust on top, cut steam vents into top crust, then brush with
egg wash.

Place skillet on a rimmed sheet pan and bake until pastry is golden and filling is bubbly, 20 to 25 minutes. Serve immediately.
